---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ServiceExplore from '../../components/ServiceExplore.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Root Canal Therapy — Oasis Dental Care, Huntington Beach"
  description="Gentle root canal therapy in Huntington Beach. Relieve pain and save your tooth with Dr. Jason Fu at Oasis Dental Care. Call (714) 893-2106."
  page="services"
>

<section class="phero">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="crumbs"><a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><a href="/services">Services</a><span class="sep">/</span><span style="color:#cfe6e2">Root Canal Therapy</span></div>
    <span class="tag">Restorative dentistry</span>
    <h1>Root Canal Therapy</h1>
    <p>Relieve pain and save your natural tooth.</p>
    <div class="acts">
      <a class="btn" href="/contact">Schedule an evaluation <svg class="ico" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6"/></svg></a>
      <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="tel:7148932106">Call (714) 893-2106</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="pad">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="split">
      <div>

        <div class="img-ph reveal">
          <div class="img-ph-ic"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="3"/><circle cx="8.5" cy="9" r="1.5"/><path d="m21 15-5-5L5 21"/></svg></div>
          <span class="img-ph-lbl">Photo placeholder</span>
          <span class="img-ph-desc">Calm, reassuring clinical shot — avoid anything alarming</span>
        </div>

        <div class="prose reveal">
          <span class="tag">Overview</span>
          <h2>Modern root canal therapy is nothing to fear.</h2>
          <p>Root canal therapy treats infection inside the tooth, relieves pain, and prevents the need for extraction. It preserves your natural tooth structure while restoring comfort and function.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="prose reveal" style="margin-top:48px">
          <h3>What Is Root Canal Therapy?</h3>
          <p>When infection reaches the pulp (inner tissue) of a tooth, it causes pain and can spread. During a root canal, Dr. Fu removes the infected tissue, cleans the canal, and seals the tooth. A crown is usually placed afterward to protect it.</p>

          <div class="img-ph reveal">
            <div class="img-ph-ic"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="3"/><circle cx="8.5" cy="9" r="1.5"/><path d="m21 15-5-5L5 21"/></svg></div>
            <span class="img-ph-lbl">Photo placeholder</span>
            <span class="img-ph-desc">Calming clinical photo, or simple tooth cross-section diagram</span>
          </div>

          <h3>Signs You May Need One</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Persistent or severe toothache</li>
            <li>Prolonged sensitivity to heat or cold</li>
            <li>Darkening of the tooth</li>
            <li>Swelling or tenderness in nearby gums</li>
            <li>A pimple-like bump on the gum</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Does It Hurt?</h3>
          <p>Modern root canal therapy is far more comfortable than its reputation suggests. Local anesthesia numbs the area completely, and many patients say the procedure felt no different from getting a filling. Post-procedure soreness is normal and typically resolves within a few days.</p>

          <div class="img-ph reveal">
            <div class="img-ph-ic"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="3"/><circle cx="8.5" cy="9" r="1.5"/><path d="m21 15-5-5L5 21"/></svg></div>
            <span class="img-ph-lbl">Photo placeholder</span>
            <span class="img-ph-desc">Patient at ease in chair, Dr. Fu present — calm and reassuring</span>
          </div>

          <h3>What Happens Next?</h3>
          <p>After root canal therapy, a crown is usually recommended to restore the tooth's strength. We'll walk you through aftercare instructions and schedule the final restoration.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="reveal" style="margin-top:48px">
          <span class="tag">Common questions</span>
          <h2 class="prose" style="margin-top:8px">Good to know.</h2>
          <div class="faq">
            <details open><summary>Does a root canal hurt?</summary><p>No—the area is fully numbed before treatment. Most patients are surprised by how comfortable the procedure actually is.</p></details>
            <details><summary>How long does root canal therapy take?</summary><p>Most root canals are completed in one or two appointments, each lasting about 60–90 minutes depending on the complexity of the tooth.</p></details>
            <details><summary>What happens after my root canal?</summary><p>You may experience mild soreness for a day or two, manageable with over-the-counter pain relief. We'll schedule a follow-up to place a permanent crown.</p></details>
            <details><summary>Will I need a crown after my root canal?</summary><p>In most cases, yes. A crown protects the treated tooth from fracture and restores its full function. We'll factor this into your treatment plan from the start.</p></details>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <aside>
        <div class="scard reveal">
          <div class="hd"><div class="grid-ov"></div><h3>Schedule an evaluation</h3><p>Root canal appointments typically 60–90 min</p></div>
          <div class="bd">
            <div class="row"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/><path d="M12 7v5l3 2"/></svg><span>Most cases completed in 1–2 visits</span></div>
            <div class="row"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M20 6 9 17l-5-5"/></svg><span>Most insurance accepted &amp; verified</span></div>
            <div class="row"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 2 4 5v6c0 5 3.5 9 8 11 4.5-2 8-6 8-11V5l-8-3z"/></svg><span>Gentle, precision-focused technique</span></div>
            <div class="divider"></div>
            <a class="btn" href="/contact">Schedule an Evaluation</a>
            <a class="btn btn-out" href="tel:7148932106" style="justify-content:center">Call (714) 893-2106</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<ServiceExplore />

</Layout>
